Tesla Shanghai Production Line

Model 3/Y Assembly Process

Battery Pack Integration: CATL cells arrive from Lingang (co-located), Fuding, or Liyang facilities. Pack assembly happens on-site with 95% localized components including BMS, cooling systems, and structural elements.

Body & Chassis: Stamping, welding, and casting operations produce the unibody structure. The mega-casting machines create front and rear underbody sections, reducing parts from 70+ to just 2 pieces.

Power Electronics: SiC inverters from Wuhan and Shaoxing fabs enable higher efficiency. Drive units, onboard chargers, and DC-DC converters are integrated with the battery pack and motor assembly.

Final Assembly: Interior trim, seats, glass, wheels, and electronics from 60+ tier-1 suppliers converge on the line. Quality control, software flashing, and testing complete before vehicles roll off for domestic delivery or export via Shanghai port.

Production cycle: ~10 hours per vehicle | Daily output: ~2,000 units | Export destinations: Europe, Asia-Pacific, Middle East
